Typhoon approaches Japan with 105 mph winds . Typhoon Opal , with 105 mph winds , is approaching Japan and will make landfall within 24 hours in southern Honshu , independent forecaster Weather Services Corporation said . Opal , near 29n / 134e and moving north at 20 mph , may weaken slightly before landfall and will then accelerate northwards through Japan . The storm will likely cause major damage to coastal property at and east of the landfall in southern Honshu , with winds up to 120 mph and a storm surge of up to 25 feet . As the system moves northward the winds will diminish but very heavy to torrential rains will continue . Large areas of Honshu Japan can expect rains of 5 to 15 inches , bringing flooding and possible mudslides . 
